//! Zig port of SQLite's compile-time-option reporting (src/ctime.c).
//!
//! Upstream `ctime.c` is GENERATED by `tool/mkctimec.tcl`: it is a big,
//! A-Z-sorted `static const char * const sqlite3azCompileOpt[]` whose entries
//! are each guarded by an `#ifdef`, plus the single non-static function
//! `sqlite3CompileOptions(int*)`. Which strings are emitted depends ENTIRELY on
//! which `SQLITE_*` macros are defined for THIS build, so we do not transcribe
//! the `#ifdef` maze. Instead the exact two string lists below were derived
//! EMPIRICALLY by compiling the real `vendor/tsrc/ctime.c` with this project's
//! flags (see the build-derivation note further down) and dumping the array.
//!
//! Only `sqlite3CompileOptions` lives here. The public APIs
//! `sqlite3_compileoption_get` / `sqlite3_compileoption_used` are part of
//! main.c and are already ported in src/main.zig (they call back into the
//! `sqlite3CompileOptions` exported here).
//!
//! SQLITE_OMIT_COMPILEOPTION_DIAGS is OFF in this build, so the function is
//! present (the `#ifndef` guard around the whole file is satisfied).
//!
//! The strings are stored WITHOUT the "SQLITE_" prefix (the C generator strips
//! it), MUST stay A-Z sorted in C/ASCII (strcmp) order, and MUST match the C
//! output order exactly — `sqlite3_compileoption_used` (in main.zig) scans this
//! array and relies on the entries being the canonical names.
//!
//! Two configs, comptime-selected via `@import("config")`:
//!   * production library   — `sqlite_flags` in build.zig (56 entries)
//!   * testfixture (--dev)  — production + SQLITE_DEBUG + SQLITE_TEST,
//!     which add three entries: DEBUG, NEED_ERR_NAME, TEST (59 entries).
//! `config.sqlite_debug` and `config.sqlite_test` are both set true only for the
//! testfixture build (tools/tcltest.sh), false for the production library, so
//! one object serves both configurations.
//!
//! Build-derivation note (how the lists below were obtained):
//!   A probe that `#include "ctime.c"` and prints every entry of
//!   `sqlite3CompileOptions()` was compiled with `zig cc` and this project's
//!   exact flags. Production:
//!     zig cc -I vendor/tsrc <sqlite_flags> probe.c   -> 56 entries
//!   Testfixture (adds -DSQLITE_DEBUG -DSQLITE_TEST):
//!     zig cc -I vendor/tsrc <sqlite_flags> -DSQLITE_DEBUG -DSQLITE_TEST probe.c
//!                                                    -> 59 entries
//!   Both outputs are A-Z sorted (verified with `LC_ALL=C sort`).
//!
//! COMPILER string: the C generator bakes in the version of the compiler that
//! built the object (`COMPILER=clang-MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH` under clang). The C
//! translation units in this project are built by `zig cc`, whose clang reports
//! `clang-22.1.4` for this toolchain. We bake the same value here so the entry
//! matches the C-built artifact byte-for-byte. No test pins this value (the only
//! upstream references are hardcoded corrupt-DB blobs), so it is purely a
//! build-environment constant exactly like the C `COMPILER=gcc-...` it replaces.

const config = @import("config");

/// `COMPILER=` entry. Mirrors what `zig cc`'s clang emits for this toolchain;
/// see the COMPILER note in the file header.
const compiler_opt: [*:0]const u8 = "COMPILER=clang-22.1.4";

